<EFX_MANAGEMENTS_DISCUSSION>
<A NAME="FIS_MANAGEMENTS_DISCUSSION"></A>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=1>
<A NAME="A2230524Z10-K_HTM_DM41701_ITEM_7__MANAGEMENT_S_DISCUSSIO__ITE03668">
</A>
<A NAME="A2230524Z10-K_HTM_TOC_DM41701_2">
</A>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
	ITEM 7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;MANAGEMENT'S DISCUSSION AND ANALYSIS OF FINANCIAL CONDITION AND RESULTS OF OPERATIONS
<BR>
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	This Management's Discussion and Analysis of Financial Condition and Results of Operations ("MD&amp;A") is intended to provide a reader of
	our financial statements with a narrative from the perspective of management on our financial condition, results of operations, liquidity and certain other factors that may affect our future results.
	Unless expressly stated otherwise, the comparisons presented in this MD&amp;A refer to the prior fiscal year. Statements that are not historical are forward-looking and involve risks and uncertainties,
	including those discussed in Part&nbsp;I, Item&nbsp;1A, "Risk Factors" and elsewhere in this report. These risks could cause our actual results to differ materially from any future performance
	suggested below.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-LEFT:11.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-11.0PT;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:11.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-11.0PT;" -->
	OVERVIEW
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	The Toro Company is in the business of designing, manufacturing, and marketing professional turf maintenance equipment and services,
	turf irrigation systems, landscaping equipment and lighting products, snow and ice management products, agricultural micro-irrigation systems, rental and specialty construction equipment, and
	residential yard and snow thrower products. We sell our products worldwide through a network of distributors, dealers, hardware retailers, home centers, mass retailers, and online. Our businesses are
	organized into three reportable business segments: Professional, Residential, and Distribution. Our Distribution segment, which consists of our company-owned domestic distributorship, has been
	combined with our corporate activities and is shown as "Other." We strive to provide innovative, well-built, and dependable products supported by an extensive
</FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	27
</FONT>
</P>
<HR NOSHADE>
<P STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;PAGE-BREAK-BEFORE:ALWAYS'>
</P>
<!-- ZEQ.=1,SEQ=27,EFW="2230524",CP="TORO COMPANY",DN="1",CHK=405886,FOLIO='27',FILE='DISK126:[16ZCF1.16ZCF41701]DM41701A.;39',USER='VRIVERA',CD='22-DEC-2016;05:08' -->
<A NAME="A2230524Z10-K_HTM_PAGE_DM41701_1_28">
</A>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<A HREF="#A2230524Z10-K_HTM_BG41701A_MAIN_TOC">
	Table of Contents
</A>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	service
	network. A significant portion of our net sales has historically been, and we expect will continue to be, attributable to new and enhanced products. We define new products as those introduced
	in the current and previous two fiscal years. Shares and per share data have been adjusted for all periods presented to reflect the impact of our two-for-one stock split effective September&nbsp;16,
	2016.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-LEFT:10.5PT;TEXT-INDENT:-10.5PT;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<A NAME="A2230524Z10-K_HTM_DM41701_SUMMARY_OF_FISCAL_2016_RESULTS">
</A>
<A NAME="A2230524Z10-K_HTM_TOC_DM41701_3">
</A>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:10.5PT;TEXT-INDENT:-10.5PT;" -->
	Summary of Fiscal 2016 Results
<BR>
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	In fiscal 2016, we achieved net sales of $2,392.2&nbsp;million and net earnings growth of 14.6&nbsp;percent. Our fiscal 2016
	results included the following items of significance:
</FONT>
</P>
<DL COMPACT>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-11PT;'>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&#149;
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Net sales for fiscal 2016 increased by 0.1&nbsp;percent compared to fiscal 2015 to $2,392.2&nbsp;million. Foreign currency exchange
	rate fluctuations negatively impacted our net sales growth by 1.3&nbsp;percent. The sales increase was primarily attributable to strong demand of our Professional segment products including the
	successful introduction of new innovative products, primarily offset by lower Residential segment sales driven mainly by decreased pre-season snow products demand.
</FONT>
</DD>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-11PT;'>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&#149;
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Professional segment
	net sales grew 4.0&nbsp;percent in fiscal 2016 compared to fiscal 2015. Sales increased primarily from strong
	demand for our golf and landscape contractor equipment, increased product placement of our micro-irrigation products, along with continued growth in our rental and specialty construction businesses.
</FONT>
</DD>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-11PT;'>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&#149;
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Residential segment net sales decreased 7.8&nbsp;percent in fiscal 2016 compared to fiscal 2015, primarily due to lower sales of snow
	products and decreased shipments of zero-turn radius riding mowers, partially offset by increased shipments of walk power mowers.
</FONT>
</DD>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-11PT;'>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&#149;
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	International net sales for fiscal 2016 decreased by
	5.1&nbsp;percent compared to fiscal 2015 mainly due to changes in foreign
	currency exchange rates that reduced our total net sales by approximately $30.6&nbsp;million in fiscal 2016. International net sales comprised 24.2&nbsp;percent of our total consolidated net sales
	in fiscal 2016 compared to 25.5&nbsp;percent in fiscal 2015 and 28.7&nbsp;percent in fiscal 2014. These declines were primarily the result of foreign currency exchange rate changes.
</FONT>
</DD>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-11PT;'>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&#149;
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Fiscal 2016 net earnings of $231.0&nbsp;million increased 14.6&nbsp;percent compared to fiscal 2015, and diluted net earnings per
	share increased 15.7&nbsp;percent to $2.06 in fiscal 2016 compared to $1.78 in fiscal 2015.
</FONT>
</DD>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-11PT;'>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&#149;
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Gross margin was 36.6&nbsp;percent in fiscal 2016, an increase of 160 basis points from
	35.0&nbsp;percent in fiscal 2015. This
	increase was primarily the result of favorable commodity costs and enhanced productivity, as well as favorable segment mix.
</FONT>
</DD>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-11PT;'>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&#149;
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Selling, general, and administrative ("SG&amp;A") expense was
	up 0.6&nbsp;percent in fiscal 2016 compared to fiscal 2015, or up
	10&nbsp;basis points to 22.6&nbsp;percent.
</FONT>
</DD>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-11PT;'>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&#149;
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Receivables decreased by 7.8&nbsp;percent as of the end of fiscal 2016 compared to the end of fiscal 2015 primarily as a result of
	more receivables financed through Red Iron. Our inventory levels were down by 8.2&nbsp;percent as of the end of fiscal 2016 compared to the end of fiscal 2015 primarily due to focused production
	planning in the latter half of fiscal 2016. Average net working capital (net accounts receivable plus net inventory less trade payables) as a percent of net sales was 15.9&nbsp;percent as of the end
	of fiscal 2016 compared to 16.0&nbsp;percent as of the end of fiscal 2015. Our domestic field inventory levels were up as of the end of fiscal 2016 compared to the end of fiscal 2015, primarily due
	to higher levels in the Professional segment with higher retail demand and anticipated strong retail of new products in fiscal 2017.
</FONT>
</DD>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-11PT;'>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&#149;
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	We continued our history of paying quarterly cash
	dividends in fiscal 2016. We increased our fiscal 2016 quarterly cash dividend by
	20&nbsp;percent to $0.15 per share compared to our quarterly cash dividend in fiscal 2015 of $0.125 per share.
</FONT>
</DD>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-11PT;'>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&#149;
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Our stock repurchase program returned $112.0&nbsp;million to our
	shareholders during fiscal 2016, which reduced our number of shares
	outstanding. This reduction resulted in a benefit to our diluted net earnings per share of $0.03 per share in fiscal 2016 compared to fiscal 2015.
</FONT>
</DD>
</DL>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-LEFT:10.5PT;TEXT-INDENT:-10.5PT;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<A NAME="A2230524Z10-K_HTM_DM41701_DESTINATION_PRIME">
</A>
<A NAME="A2230524Z10-K_HTM_TOC_DM41701_4">
</A>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:10.5PT;TEXT-INDENT:-10.5PT;" -->
	Destination PRIME
<BR>
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Our current multi-year initiative, "Destination PRIME," began our journey into our second century. Similar to our previous Destination
	2014 initiative, this three-year initiative is intended to help us drive revenue and earnings growth and further improve productivity, while also continuing our century-long commitment to innovation,
	relationships, and excellence. Through our Destination PRIME initiative, we will strive to achieve our goals by pursuing a progression of milestones for organic revenue growth, operating earnings, and
	working capital.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<I>
	Organic Revenue Growth.
</I>
</B>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	We intend to pursue strategic growth of our existing businesses and product categories with an annual organic revenue growth goal.
	The organic revenue growth goal of our Destination PRIME initiative is to achieve at least five percent organic revenue growth each fiscal year of this initiative. We define organic revenue growth as
	the increase in net sales, less
	net sales from acquisitions that occurred in the prior twelve-month period. In both fiscal 2016 and fiscal 2015, we fell short of this goal by achieving 0.1&nbsp;percent and 4.1&nbsp;percent
	organic revenue growth, respectively.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<I>
	Operating Earnings.
</I>
</B>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	The operating earnings goal is to raise operating earnings as a percentage of net sales to 13&nbsp;percent or higher by the end of
	fiscal 2017. In fiscal 2016, we achieved this goal as we realized 14.0&nbsp;percent of operating earnings as a percentage of net sales. In fiscal 2015, we realized 12.5&nbsp;percent of operating
	earnings as a percentage of net sales.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<I>
	Working Capital.
</I>
</B>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	The working capital goal of our Destination PRIME initiative is to drive down average net working capital as
</FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	28
</FONT>
</P>
<HR NOSHADE>
<P STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;PAGE-BREAK-BEFORE:ALWAYS'>
</P>
<!-- ZEQ.=2,SEQ=28,EFW="2230524",CP="TORO COMPANY",DN="1",CHK=702193,FOLIO='28',FILE='DISK126:[16ZCF1.16ZCF41701]DM41701A.;39',USER='VRIVERA',CD='22-DEC-2016;05:08' -->
<A NAME="A2230524Z10-K_HTM_PAGE_DM41701_1_29">
</A>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<A HREF="#A2230524Z10-K_HTM_BG41701A_MAIN_TOC">
	Table of Contents
</A>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	a
	percentage of net sales to 13&nbsp;percent or lower by the end of fiscal 2017. In fiscal 2016 and fiscal 2015, our average net working capital as a percentage of net sales was 15.9&nbsp;percent
	and 16.0&nbsp;percent, respectively.
</FONT>
</P>
<EFX_RESULTS_OF_OPERATIONS>
<A NAME="FIS_RESULTS_OF_OPERATIONS"></A>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-LEFT:11.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-11.0PT;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:11.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-11.0PT;" -->
	RESULTS OF OPERATIONS
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Fiscal 2016 net earnings were $231.0&nbsp;million compared to $201.6&nbsp;million in fiscal 2015, an increase of
	14.6&nbsp;percent. Fiscal 2016 diluted net earnings per share were $2.06, an increase of 15.7&nbsp;percent from $1.78 per share in fiscal 2015. The primary factors contributing to the net earnings
	increase were gross margin improvement and a decrease in our effective tax rate. However, these improvements were partially offset by an increase in our SG&amp;A expense. Our net earnings per diluted
	share were also benefited by $0.03 per share in fiscal 2016 compared to fiscal 2015 as a result of reduced shares outstanding from repurchases of our common stock.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Fiscal
	2015 net earnings were $201.6&nbsp;million compared to $173.9&nbsp;million in fiscal 2014, an increase of 15.9&nbsp;percent. Fiscal 2015 diluted net earnings per share were $1.78, an
	increase of 17.5&nbsp;percent from $1.51 per share in fiscal 2014. The primary factors contributing to the net earnings improvement were higher net sales, leveraging fixed SG&amp;A costs over higher
	sales volumes, and a decrease in our effective tax rate. However, these improvements were partially offset by a decline in our gross margin rate and an increase in interest expense. Our net earnings
	per diluted share were also benefited by $0.03 per share in fiscal 2015 compared to fiscal 2014 as a result of reduced shares outstanding from repurchases of our common stock.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	The
	following table summarizes our results of operations as a percentage of our consolidated net sales.
</FONT>
</P>

<TD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;BACKGROUND-COLOR:#D1ECFA;">
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;MARGIN-LEFT:6PT;TEXT-INDENT:-6PT;">
<FONT SIZE=1>
<B>
</B>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=1>
<B>
<!-- COMMAND=ADD_GRID,"BACKGROUND-COLOR:#D1ECFA;" -->
	Net sales
</B>
</FONT>
</TD>
<TD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;BACKGROUND-COLOR:#D1ECFA;">
<FONT SIZE=1>
<B>
	&nbsp;
<!-- COMMAND=ADD_GRID,"BACKGROUND-COLOR:#D1ECFA;" -->
</B>
</FONT>
</TD>
<TD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;BACKGROUND-COLOR:#D1ECFA;">

<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<A NAME="A2230524Z10-K_HTM_DM41701_FISCAL_2016_COMPARED_WITH_FISCAL_2015">
</A>
<A NAME="A2230524Z10-K_HTM_TOC_DM41701_5">
</A>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:10.5PT;TEXT-INDENT:-10.5PT;" -->
	Fiscal 2016 Compared with Fiscal 2015
<BR>
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<I>
	Net Sales.
</I>
</B>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Worldwide net sales in fiscal 2016 were $2,392.2&nbsp;million compared to $2,390.9&nbsp;million in fiscal 2015, an increase of
	0.1&nbsp;percent. This net sales change was attributable to the following factors:
</FONT>
</P>
<DL COMPACT>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-11PT;'>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&#149;
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Increased sales of Professional segment products were driven by higher shipments and demand of golf, landscape contractor, and rental
	and specialty equipment products primarily due to continued market growth and increased demand for our innovative product offerings and the successful introduction of new products. Micro-irrigation
	and irrigation product sales also increased mainly due to improved product placement and higher project sales. However, sales of snow and ice management products were down primarily due to decreased
	pre-season demand.
</FONT>
</DD>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-11PT;'>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&#149;
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Decreased sales of Residential segment products were mainly driven by lower sales and pre-season retail demand of snow thrower
	products, decreased shipments of zero-turn radius riding mowers, and unfavorable weather conditions in many of our markets. However, sales of our walk power mowers increased mainly due to strong
	shipments driven by our innovative product offerings and favorable growing season weather in key markets.
</FONT>
</DD>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-11PT;'>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&#149;
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Our overall net sales in international markets decreased by 5.1&nbsp;percent in
	fiscal 2016 compared to fiscal 2015 due to
	unfavorable foreign currency exchange rate fluctuations that reduced our total net sales by approximately $30.6&nbsp;million in fiscal 2016.
</FONT>
</DD>
</DL>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<I>
	Gross Margin.
</I>
</B>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Gross margin represents gross profit (net sales less cost of sales) as a percentage of net sales. See Note&nbsp;1 of the Notes to
	Consolidated Financial Statements, in the section entitled "Cost of Sales," for a description of expenses included in cost of sales. Gross margin increased by 160 basis points to 36.6&nbsp;percent
	in fiscal 2016 from 35.0&nbsp;percent in fiscal 2015. This increase was mainly the result of the following factors:
</FONT>
</P>
<DL COMPACT>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-11PT;'>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&#149;
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Lower costs to purchase commodities, primarily steel and resin, and productivity improvements.
</FONT>
</DD>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-11PT;'>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&#149;
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Segment mix from a higher mix of
	Professional segment product sales.
</FONT>
</DD>
</DL>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Somewhat
	offsetting those positive factors were unfavorable foreign currency exchange rate fluctuations.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<I>
	Selling, General, and Administrative Expense.
</I>
</B>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	SG&amp;A expense increased $3.4&nbsp;million, or 0.6&nbsp;percent, in fiscal 2016 compared to fiscal 2015.
	See Note&nbsp;1 of the Notes to Consolidated Financial Statements, in the section entitled "Selling, General, and Administrative Expense," for a description of expenses included in SG&amp;A expense.
	SG&amp;A expense rate represents SG&amp;A expense as a percentage of net sales. SG&amp;A expense rate in fiscal 2016 increased 10&nbsp;basis points to 22.6&nbsp;percent compared to 22.5&nbsp;percent in
	fiscal 2015. The increase in SG&amp;A expense was driven primarily by the following factors:
</FONT>
</P>
<DL COMPACT>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-11PT;'>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&#149;
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Continued investments in engineering and new product development that resulted in higher expense of $3.8&nbsp;million.
</FONT>
</DD>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-11PT;'>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&#149;
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Increased
	warranty expense of $3.1&nbsp;million driven by higher claims experience for the year.
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
</FONT>
</DD>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-11PT;'>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&#149;
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Higher direct marketing expense of $2.2&nbsp;million mainly due to increased media spend and paid commissions.
</FONT>
</DD>
</DL>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	29
</FONT>
</P>
<HR NOSHADE>
<P STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;PAGE-BREAK-BEFORE:ALWAYS'>
</P>

<A NAME="A2230524Z10-K_HTM_PAGE_DM41701_1_30">
</A>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<A HREF="#A2230524Z10-K_HTM_BG41701A_MAIN_TOC">
	Table of Contents
</A>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Somewhat
	offsetting those increases were:
</FONT>
</P>
<DL COMPACT>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-11PT;'>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&#149;
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Decreased administrative expense of $3.4&nbsp;million.
</FONT>
</DD>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-11PT;'>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&#149;
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Decreased incentive expense of $3.3&nbsp;million due to actual performance
	against specified goals.
</FONT>
</DD>
</DL>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<I>
	Interest Expense.
</I>
</B>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Interest expense for fiscal 2016 increased $0.6&nbsp;million compared to fiscal 2015.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<I>
	Other Income, Net.
</I>
</B>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Other income, net consists mainly of our proportionate share of income or losses from equity investments (affiliates), currency
	exchange rate gains and losses, litigation settlements and recoveries, interest income, and retail financing revenue. Other income for fiscal 2016 was $15.4&nbsp;million compared to
	$10.7&nbsp;million in fiscal 2015, an increase of $4.7&nbsp;million. The increase in other income, net was primarily due to foreign currency contract exchange gains of $1.8&nbsp;million, a
	fiscal 2016 litigation recovery of $1.3&nbsp;million, and higher earnings from our equity investment in Red Iron of $1.2&nbsp;million.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<I>
	Provision for Income Taxes.
</I>
</B>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	The effective tax rate for fiscal 2016 was 30.1&nbsp;percent compared to 30.7&nbsp;percent in fiscal 2015. The decrease
	was primarily the result of more favorable one-time adjustments related to prior years, and the permanent extension of the federal research credit.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-LEFT:10.5PT;TEXT-INDENT:-10.5PT;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<A NAME="A2230524Z10-K_HTM_DM41701_FISCAL_2015_COMPARED_WITH_FISCAL_2014">
</A>
<A NAME="A2230524Z10-K_HTM_TOC_DM41701_6">
</A>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:10.5PT;TEXT-INDENT:-10.5PT;" -->
	Fiscal 2015 Compared with Fiscal 2014
<BR>
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<I>
	Net Sales.
</I>
</B>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Worldwide net sales in fiscal 2015 were $2,390.9&nbsp;million compared to $2,172.7&nbsp;million in fiscal 2014, an increase of
	10.0&nbsp;percent. This net sales change was attributable to the following factors:
</FONT>
</P>
<DL COMPACT>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-11PT;'>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&#149;
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Increased sales of Professional segment products driven by the acquisition of the BOSS business which resulted in incremental net sales
	of $128.5&nbsp;million for fiscal 2015. In addition, our Professional segment net sales were positively impacted by higher shipments of landscape contractor and rental and specialty equipment
	products due to continued market growth and increased demand for our innovative product offerings and newly introduced products. However, sales of irrigation products were down primarily due to
	unfavorable weather conditions in key markets, and sales of micro-irrigation products were lower due to unfavorable foreign currency exchange rates and continued adverse political and economic
	conditions in key international markets.
</FONT>
</DD>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-11PT;'>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&#149;
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Increased sales of Residential segment products due to strong shipments and demand for our newly introduced zero-turn radius riding and
	walk power mower products and expanded product placement. However, Residential segment net sales in Australia were down due to unfavorable foreign currency exchange rate changes.
</FONT>
</DD>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-11PT;'>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&#149;
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Our
	overall net sales in international markets slightly decreased by 1.9&nbsp;percent in fiscal 2015 compared to fiscal 2014 due to
	unfavorable foreign currency exchange rate fluctuations that reduced our total net sales by approximately $47&nbsp;million in fiscal 2015.
</FONT>
</DD>
</DL>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<I>
	Gross Margin.
</I>
</B>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Gross margin decreased by 60 basis points to 35.0&nbsp;percent in fiscal 2015 from 35.6&nbsp;percent in fiscal 2014. This decline was
	mainly the result of the following factors:
</FONT>
</P>
<DL COMPACT>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-11PT;'>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&#149;
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Unfavorable foreign currency exchange rate movements.
</FONT>
</DD>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-11PT;'>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&#149;
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Purchase accounting impact of the incremental charge for the sale of inventory
	that was written-up to fair value as a result of the
	acquisition of the BOSS business.
</FONT>
</DD>
</DL>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Somewhat
	offsetting those negative factors were:
</FONT>
</P>
<DL COMPACT>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-11PT;'>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&#149;
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Improved price realization.
</FONT>
</DD>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-11PT;'>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&#149;
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Costs for a supplier component rework issue that impacted certain walk power mowers in fiscal 2014 that
	was not repeated in fiscal
	2015.
</FONT>
</DD>
</DL>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<I>
	Selling, General, and Administrative Expense.
</I>
</B>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	SG&amp;A expense increased $26.7&nbsp;million, or 5.2&nbsp;percent, in fiscal 2015 compared to fiscal 2014.
	SG&amp;A expense rate in fiscal 2015 decreased 100 basis points to 22.5&nbsp;percent compared to 23.5&nbsp;percent in fiscal 2014 due to fixed SG&amp;A costs spread over higher sales volumes. However, the
	increase in SG&amp;A expense of $26.7&nbsp;million was driven mainly by the following factors:
</FONT>
</P>
<DL COMPACT>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-11PT;'>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&#149;
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Incremental SG&amp;A expense of $19&nbsp;million from the BOSS business.
</FONT>
</DD>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-11PT;'>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&#149;
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Increased administrative expenses of $7&nbsp;million.
</FONT>
</DD>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-11PT;'>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&#149;
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Investments in engineering and new product development that resulted in higher expense of $2&nbsp;million.
</FONT>
</DD>
</DL>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<I>
	Interest Expense.
</I>
</B>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Interest expense for fiscal 2015 increased $3.3&nbsp;million compared to fiscal 2014 due to higher levels of debt as a result of
	borrowings that were used to pay the purchase price for the BOSS business.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<I>
	Other Income, Net.
</I>
</B>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Other income for fiscal 2015 was $10.7&nbsp;million compared to $8.7&nbsp;million in fiscal 2014, an increase of
	$2.0&nbsp;million. This increase in other income, net was primarily due to higher earnings from our equity investment in Red Iron of $1.1&nbsp;million and lower foreign currency exchange rate
	losses of $0.7&nbsp;million in fiscal 2015 compared to fiscal 2014.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<I>
	Provision for Income Taxes.
</I>
</B>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	The effective tax rate for fiscal 2015 was 30.7&nbsp;percent compared to 32.2&nbsp;percent in fiscal 2014. The decrease in
	the effective tax rate was attributable to the benefit in the first quarter of fiscal 2015 for the retroactive re-enactment of the federal research credit for calendar 2014 and higher earnings in
	lower tax jurisdictions.
</FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	30
</FONT>
</P>
<HR NOSHADE>
<P STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;PAGE-BREAK-BEFORE:ALWAYS'>
</P>

<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-LEFT:11.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-11.0PT;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:11.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-11.0PT;" -->
	PERFORMANCE BY BUSINESS SEGMENT
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	As more fully described in Note&nbsp;12 of the Notes to Consolidated Financial Statements, we operate in three reportable business
	segments: Professional, Residential, and Distribution. Our Distribution segment, which consists of our company-owned domestic distributorship, has been combined with our corporate activities and is
	shown as "Other." Operating earnings for our Professional and Residential segments are defined as earnings from operations plus other income, net. Operating loss for the Other segment includes
	earnings (loss) from our wholly owned domestic distribution companies, corporate activities, other income, and interest expense. The following information provides perspective on our business
	segments' net sales and operating results.
</FONT>
</P>
<EFX_UNIDENTIFIED_TABLE>
<A NAME="FIS_UNIDENTIFIED_TABLE_11"></A>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-LEFT:10.5PT;TEXT-INDENT:-10.5PT;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<A NAME="A2230524Z10-K_HTM_DO41701_PROFESSIONAL_SEGMENT">
</A>
<A NAME="A2230524Z10-K_HTM_TOC_DO41701_1">
</A>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:10.5PT;TEXT-INDENT:-10.5PT;" -->
	Professional Segment
<BR>
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Professional segment net sales represented 71&nbsp;percent of consolidated net sales for fiscal 2016, 69&nbsp;percent for fiscal
	2015, and 68&nbsp;percent for fiscal 2014. The following table shows the Professional segment net sales, operating earnings, and operating earnings as a percent of net sales.
</FONT>
</P>

<TD STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:0PT;FONT-SIZE:1.5PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;BORDER-BOTTOM:SOLID #000000 1.0PT;">
<FONT SIZE=1>
<B>
</B>
</FONT>
	&#8203;
<!-- COMMAND=ADD_GRID,"BORDER-BOTTOM:SOLID #000000 1.0PT;" -->
<FONT>

<FONT>
<B>
<!-- COMMAND=ADD_GRID,"BORDER-BOTTOM:SOLID #000000 1.0PT;" -->
</B>
</FONT>
</TD>
<TD STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:0PT;FONT-SIZE:1.5PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;BORDER-BOTTOM:SOLID #000000 1.0PT;">

<!-- END OF USER-SPECIFIED TAGGED TABLE -->
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<I>
	Net Sales.
</I>
</B>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Worldwide net sales for the Professional segment in fiscal 2016 were up by 4.0&nbsp;percent compared to fiscal 2015 primarily as a result of the
	following factors:
</FONT>
</P>
<DL COMPACT>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-11PT;'>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&#149;
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Higher shipments of golf equipment and irrigation products, mainly due to demand for our innovative product offerings, the successful
	introduction of new products, increased golf irrigation projects, and favorable weather conditions.
</FONT>
</DD>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-11PT;'>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&#149;
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Increased sales of landscape contractor equipment driven by strong demand of our
	riding and stand-on mower product lines.
</FONT>
</DD>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-11PT;'>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&#149;
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Higher sales of micro-irrigation products which were mainly driven by improved product placement.
</FONT>
</DD>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-11PT;'>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&#149;
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Increased sales driven by strong demand and market growth for rental and specialty construction equipment, as well as positive customer
	response for new products.
</FONT>
</DD>
</DL>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Somewhat
	offsetting those positive factors were:
</FONT>
</P>
<DL COMPACT>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-11PT;'>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&#149;
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Unfavorable foreign currency exchange rate fluctuations.
</FONT>
</DD>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-11PT;'>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&#149;
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	A decline in sales of snow and ice management products which was driven
	mainly from decreased pre-season demand.
</FONT>
</DD>
</DL>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Our
	domestic field inventory levels of our Professional segment products were higher as of the end of fiscal 2016 compared to the end of fiscal 2015 due, primarily to anticipated strong shipments of
	new product introductions and higher retail demand.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Worldwide
	net sales for the Professional segment in fiscal 2015 were up by 11.0&nbsp;percent compared to fiscal 2014 primarily as a result of the following
	factors:
</FONT>
</P>
<DL COMPACT>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-11PT;'>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&#149;
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Incremental sales from the acquisition of the BOSS business of $128.5&nbsp;million.
</FONT>
</DD>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-11PT;'>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&#149;
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Higher shipments of landscape contractor
	equipment, including new and enhanced products, as contractors continued to invest in turf
	maintenance equipment.
</FONT>
</DD>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-11PT;'>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&#149;
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Increased sales driven by strong demand and market growth for rental and specialty construction equipment, as well as positive customer
	response for new products we introduced in that market.
</FONT>
</DD>
</DL>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Somewhat
	offsetting those positive factors were:
</FONT>
</P>
<DL COMPACT>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-11PT;'>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&#149;
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Unfavorable foreign currency exchange rate fluctuations.
</FONT>
</DD>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-11PT;'>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&#149;
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	A decline in sales of irrigation products due to unfavorable weather
	conditions in key markets.
</FONT>
</DD>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-11PT;'>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&#149;
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Lower sales of micro-irrigation products due to unfavorable foreign currency exchange rate fluctuations and continued adverse political
	and economic conditions in key international markets.
</FONT>
</DD>
</DL>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<I>
	Operating Earnings.
</I>
</B>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Operating earnings for the Professional segment in fiscal 2016 increased 14.3&nbsp;percent compared to fiscal 2015, primarily due to higher
	sales volumes, higher gross margin, and lower SG&amp;A expense. Expressed as a percentage of net sales, Professional segment operating margins increased by 180 basis points to 20.6&nbsp;percent in
	fiscal 2016 compared to 18.8&nbsp;percent in fiscal 2015. The following factors impacted Professional segment operating earnings as a percentage of net sales for fiscal 2016:
</FONT>
</P>
<DL COMPACT>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-11PT;'>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&#149;
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Higher gross margin in fiscal 2016 compared to fiscal 2015 mainly due to lower commodity costs and productivity improvements, as well
	as favorable product mix, partially offset by unfavorable foreign currency exchange rate fluctuations.
</FONT>
</DD>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-11PT;'>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&#149;
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	A decline in SG&amp;A expense rate in fiscal 2016 compared to fiscal 2015 due to
	lower administration costs.
</FONT>
</DD>
</DL>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Operating
	earnings for the Professional segment in fiscal 2015 increased 11.5&nbsp;percent compared to fiscal 2014 primarily due to higher sales volumes. Expressed as a percentage of net sales,
	Professional segment operating margins slightly increased by 10 basis points to 18.8&nbsp;percent in fiscal 2015 compared to 18.7&nbsp;percent in fiscal 2014. The following factors impacted
	Professional segment operating earnings as a percentage of net sales for fiscal 2015:
</FONT>
</P>
<DL COMPACT>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-11PT;'>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&#149;
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Lower gross margin in fiscal 2015 compared to fiscal 2014 mainly due to unfavorable foreign currency exchange rate movements and the
	purchase accounting impact for the acquisition of the BOSS business, as previously discussed.
</FONT>
</DD>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-11PT;'>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&#149;
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	A decline in SG&amp;A expense rate in fiscal 2015 compared to fiscal 2014 due to further
	leveraging fixed SG&amp;A costs over higher sales
	volumes.
</FONT>
</DD>
</DL>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	31
</FONT>
</P>
<HR NOSHADE>
<P STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;PAGE-BREAK-BEFORE:ALWAYS'>

	$

<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<I>
	Net Sales.
</I>
</B>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Worldwide net sales for the Residential segment in fiscal 2016 were down by 7.8&nbsp;percent compared to fiscal 2015 primarily as a result of the
	following factors:
</FONT>
</P>
<DL COMPACT>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-11PT;'>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&#149;
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Decreased shipments and lower retail demand of snow products due to low snowfall totals in the 2015/2016 season.
</FONT>
</DD>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-11PT;'>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&#149;
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Lower sales of
	zero-turn radius riding mowers primarily driven by variable weather conditions throughout the year and a slight
	reduction in retail placement.
</FONT>
</DD>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-11PT;'>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&#149;
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Unfavorable weather conditions in many of our markets.
</FONT>
</DD>
</DL>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Somewhat
	offsetting the decrease in Residential segment net sales were higher sales of walk power mowers driven by increased demand for our product offerings and strong customer response for our
	innovative models, including our SMARTSTOW&reg; and all-wheel drive models.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Our
	domestic field inventory levels of our Residential segment products were lower as of the end of fiscal 2016 compared to the end of fiscal 2015 primarily due to decreased pre-season snow thrower
	product channel demand for the 2016-2017 winter season and inventory sell-through of walk power mowers from a strong fall growing season.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Worldwide
	net sales for the Residential segment in fiscal 2015 were up by 7.9&nbsp;percent compared to fiscal 2014 primarily as a result of the following
	factors:
</FONT>
</P>
<DL COMPACT>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-11PT;'>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&#149;
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Increased shipments driven by strong retail demand and additional product placement for our new platform of zero-turn radius riding
	mowers.
</FONT>
</DD>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-11PT;'>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&#149;
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Higher sales of walk power mowers due to enhanced product placement and increased demand for our product offerings, including our new
	all-wheel drive model.
</FONT>
</DD>
</DL>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Somewhat
	offsetting the increase in Residential segment net sales was a decline in sales in Australia from unfavorable foreign currency exchange rate fluctuations.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<I>
	Operating Earnings.
</I>
</B>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Operating earnings for the Residential segment in fiscal 2016 decreased 13.3&nbsp;percent compared to fiscal 2015. Expressed as a percentage
	of net sales, Residential segment operating margins decreased 70 basis points to 11.0&nbsp;percent in fiscal 2016 compared to 11.7&nbsp;percent in fiscal 2015. The following factors impacted
	Residential segment operating earnings:
</FONT>
</P>
<DL COMPACT>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-11PT;'>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&#149;
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Higher gross margin in fiscal 2016 compared to fiscal 2015 mainly due to lower commodity costs and freight expense, partially offset by
	unfavorable foreign currency exchange rate fluctuations.
</FONT>
</DD>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-11PT;'>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&#149;
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Increased SG&amp;A expense rate attributable to lower sales as well as increased engineering, marketing and warehousing
	expenses.
</FONT>
</DD>
</DL>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Operating
	earnings for the Residential segment in fiscal 2015 increased 10.5&nbsp;percent compared to fiscal 2014. Expressed as a percentage of net sales, Residential segment operating margins
	increased 30 basis points to 11.7&nbsp;percent in fiscal 2015 compared to 11.4&nbsp;percent in fiscal 2014. The following factors impacted Residential segment operating
	earnings:
</FONT>
</P>
<DL COMPACT>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-11PT;'>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&#149;
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Lower gross margins primarily from unfavorable foreign currency exchange rate fluctuations and increased manufacturing expenses.
</FONT>
</DD>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-11PT;'>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&#149;
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Lower SG&amp;A expense rate attributable to further leveraging of fixed SG&amp;A costs over higher sales volumes.
</FONT>
</DD>
</DL>
<EFX_UNIDENTIFIED_TABLE>
<A NAME="FIS_UNIDENTIFIED_TABLE_13"></A>

<FONT SIZE=2>
	Other segment net sales, which includes our company-owned domestic distributors, represented 1&nbsp;percent of consolidated net
	sales for each of fiscal 2016, 2015, and 2014. During the first quarter of fiscal 2016, we sold our Northwestern U.S. distribution company. The following table shows the other segment net sales and
	operating losses.
</FONT>
</P>

<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<I>
	Net Sales.
</I>
</B>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Net sales for the Other segment includes sales from our wholly owned domestic distribution companies less sales from the Professional and Residential
	segments to those distribution companies. The Other segment net sales in fiscal 2016 were down $7.8&nbsp;million compared to fiscal 2015, primarily due to the sale of our Northwestern U.S.
	distribution company.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	The
	Other segment net sales in fiscal 2015 were up by $2.8&nbsp;million compared to fiscal 2014 due to higher sales volumes driven by strong demand for golf and grounds equipment at our
	company-owned distribution companies.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<I>
	Operating Loss.
</I>
</B>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Operating loss for the Other segment in fiscal 2016 decreased by 6.5&nbsp;percent compared to fiscal 2015. This loss
</FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	32
</FONT>
</P>
<HR NOSHADE>
<P STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;PAGE-BREAK-BEFORE:ALWAYS'>
</P>
<!-- ZEQ.=2,SEQ=32,EFW="2230524",CP="TORO COMPANY",DN="1",CHK=551689,FOLIO='32',FILE='DISK126:[16ZCF1.16ZCF41701]DO41701A.;37',USER='VRIVERA',CD='22-DEC-2016;05:11' -->
<A NAME="A2230524Z10-K_HTM_PAGE_DO41701_1_33">
</A>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<A HREF="#A2230524Z10-K_HTM_BG41701A_MAIN_TOC">
	Table of Contents
</A>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	decrease
	was primarily attributable to increased income from our investment in Red Iron and a fiscal 2016 litigation settlement recovery.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Operating
	loss for the Other segment in fiscal 2015 increased by 5.3&nbsp;percent compared to fiscal 2014. This loss increase was primarily attributable to an increase in interest expense and higher
	administrative expenses.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-LEFT:11.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-11.0PT;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:11.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-11.0PT;" -->
	FINANCIAL CONDITION
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-LEFT:10.5PT;TEXT-INDENT:-10.5PT;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<A NAME="A2230524Z10-K_HTM_DO41701_WORKING_CAPITAL">
</A>
<A NAME="A2230524Z10-K_HTM_TOC_DO41701_4">
</A>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:10.5PT;TEXT-INDENT:-10.5PT;" -->
	Working Capital
<BR>
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	During fiscal 2016, our average net working capital (net accounts receivable plus net inventory less accounts payable) as a percentage
	of net sales decreased slightly mainly due to lower average net receivables and higher average
	accounts payable levels. As of the end of fiscal 2016, our average net working capital decreased to 15.9&nbsp;percent compared to 16.0&nbsp;percent as of the end of fiscal 2015.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	The
	following table highlights several key measures of our working capital performance.
</FONT>
</P>

<!-- END OF USER-SPECIFIED TAGGED TABLE -->
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	The
	following factors impacted our working capital:
</FONT>
</P>
<DL COMPACT>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-11PT;'>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&#149;
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Average net receivables decreased by 6.5&nbsp;percent in fiscal 2016 compared to fiscal 2015 as more receivables were financed
	through Red Iron. Our average days outstanding for receivables decreased to 31.4&nbsp;days in fiscal 2016 compared to 33.6&nbsp;days in fiscal 2015.
</FONT>
</DD>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-11PT;'>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&#149;
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Average inventories increased by
	5.3&nbsp;percent in fiscal 2016 compared to fiscal 2015. Inventory levels as of the end of fiscal
	2016 compared to the end of fiscal 2015 were down by $27.5&nbsp;million, or 8.2&nbsp;percent, primarily due to efforts to reduce high inventory levels in early fiscal 2016 through focused
	production planning in the latter half of fiscal 2016.
</FONT>
</DD>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-11PT;'>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&#149;
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Average accounts payable increased by 2.9&nbsp;percent in fiscal 2016 compared to fiscal 2015, mainly due to initiatives to
	increase
	days payables outstanding, which included extending payment terms with suppliers.
</FONT>
</DD>
</DL>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	In
	fiscal 2017, we plan to place increased emphasis on improving asset utilization with a focus on reducing the amount of working capital in the supply chain, adjusting production plans, and
	maintaining or improving order replenishment and service levels to end users. We anticipate our average net working capital as a percentage of net sales in fiscal 2017 to decrease as compared to
	fiscal 2016. We plan to place continued importance on managing our average receivables and payables. Additionally, we expect improvements in our average inventory levels primarily driven by increased
	focus and coordination between our businesses and operations.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-LEFT:10.5PT;TEXT-INDENT:-10.5PT;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<A NAME="A2230524Z10-K_HTM_DO41701_CAPITAL_EXPENDITURES_AND_OTHER_LONG-TERM_ASSETS">
</A>
<A NAME="A2230524Z10-K_HTM_TOC_DO41701_5">
</A>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:10.5PT;TEXT-INDENT:-10.5PT;" -->
	Capital Expenditures and Other Long-Term Assets
<BR>
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Fiscal 2016 capital expenditures of $50.7&nbsp;million were lower by $5.7&nbsp;million compared to fiscal 2015. This decrease was
	primarily attributable to the fiscal 2015 renovation of a portion of our original corporate facility to accommodate additional expansion needs for our product development and test capacities. Capital
	expenditures for fiscal 2017 are planned to be approximately $65&nbsp;million as we plan to invest in new product tooling, new technology in production processes and equipment, replacement of
	production equipment, and investments in new and existing facilities.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Long-term
	assets as of October&nbsp;31, 2016 were $608.5&nbsp;million compared to $631.1&nbsp;million as of October&nbsp;31, 2015, a decrease of $22.6&nbsp;million. This decrease was driven
	mainly by amortization expense of intangible assets and decreases in deferred tax assets. Included in long-term assets as of October&nbsp;31, 2016 was goodwill in the amount of
	$194.8&nbsp;million. Based on our annual impairment analysis, we determined there was no goodwill impairment for any of our reporting units as their related fair values were substantially in excess
	of their carrying values.
</FONT>
</P>
<EFX_UNIDENTIFIED_TABLE>

<!-- END OF USER-SPECIFIED TAGGED TABLE -->
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<I>
	Cash Flows from Operating Activities.
</I>
</B>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Our primary source of funds is cash generated from operations. In fiscal 2016, cash provided by operating activities increased
	$125.1&nbsp;million, or 52.8&nbsp;percent, from fiscal 2015. This increase was mainly due to lower net receivables as more net receivables were financed through Red Iron and favorable movement in
	net inventories from focused production planning in the latter half of fiscal 2016.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	In
	fiscal 2015, cash provided by operating activities increased $54.5&nbsp;million, or 29.9&nbsp;percent, from fiscal 2014. This increase was mainly due to higher net earnings and a smaller
	increase in working capital needs, as well as higher accounts payable and accrued liabilities.
</FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	33
</FONT>
</P>
<HR NOSHADE>
<P STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;PAGE-BREAK-BEFORE:ALWAYS'>
</P>
<!-- ZEQ.=3,SEQ=33,EFW="2230524",CP="TORO COMPANY",DN="1",CHK=876020,FOLIO='33',FILE='DISK126:[16ZCF1.16ZCF41701]DO41701A.;37',USER='VRIVERA',CD='22-DEC-2016;05:11' -->
<A NAME="A2230524Z10-K_HTM_PAGE_DO41701_1_34">
</A>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<A HREF="#A2230524Z10-K_HTM_BG41701A_MAIN_TOC">
	Table of Contents
</A>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<I>
	Cash Flows from Investing Activities.
</I>
</B>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Capital expenditures and acquisitions are a significant use of our capital resources. These investments are intended to enable
	sales growth in new and expanding markets, help us to meet product demand, and increase our manufacturing efficiencies and capacity. Cash used in investing activities in fiscal 2016 decreased
	$211.2&nbsp;million from fiscal 2015 due to cash utilized in fiscal 2015 for the acquisition of the BOSS business and lower purchases of property, plant, and equipment, partially offset by increased
	distributions from our joint venture with Red Iron and proceeds from the sale of our Northwestern distribution company in fiscal 2016.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Cash
	used in investing activities in fiscal 2015 increased $184.6&nbsp;million from fiscal 2014 due to cash utilized for the acquisition of the BOSS business, partially offset by lower purchases of
	property, plant, and equipment.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<I>
	Cash Flows from Financing Activities.
</I>
</B>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Cash used in financing activities in fiscal 2016 was $170.4&nbsp;million compared $173.4&nbsp;million in fiscal 2015. The
	decrease in cash used in financing activities was mainly due to favorable benefits from stock-based compensation and less cash utilized for repayments of debt in fiscal 2016 compared fiscal 2015.
	Partially offsetting this decrease was an increase in cash dividends paid on our common stock and higher amounts of cash utilized for common stock repurchases in fiscal 2016 compared to fiscal 2015.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Cash
	used in financing activities in fiscal 2015 was $173.4&nbsp;million compared to cash provided by financing activities of $17.0&nbsp;million in fiscal 2014. The increase in cash used in
	financing activities was mainly due to repayments of debt in fiscal 2015 compared to cash received from borrowings of debt in fiscal 2014. Additionally, an increase in cash dividends paid on our
	common stock and higher amounts of cash utilized for stock repurchases in fiscal 2015 compared to fiscal 2014 contributed to the increase in cash used in financing activities.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<I>
	Cash and Cash Equivalents.
</I>
</B>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Cash and cash equivalents as of the end of fiscal 2016 were higher by $147.3&nbsp;million compared to the end of fiscal 2015.
</FONT>
</P>
</EFX_RESULTS_OF_OPERATIONS>
<EFX_LIQUIDITY_CAPITAL>
<A NAME="FIS_LIQUIDITY_CAPITAL"></A>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-LEFT:10.5PT;TEXT-INDENT:-10.5PT;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<A NAME="A2230524Z10-K_HTM_DO41701_LIQUIDITY_AND_CAPITAL_RESOURCES">
</A>
<A NAME="A2230524Z10-K_HTM_TOC_DO41701_7">
</A>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:10.5PT;TEXT-INDENT:-10.5PT;" -->
	Liquidity and Capital Resources
<BR>
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Our businesses are seasonally working capital intensive and require funding for purchases of raw materials used in production,
	replacement parts inventory, payroll and other administrative costs, capital expenditures, establishment of new facilities, expansion and renovation of existing facilities, as well as for financing
	receivables from customers that are not financed with Red Iron. Our accounts receivable balances historically increase between January and April as a result of typically higher sales volumes and
	extended payment terms made available to our customers, and typically decrease between May and December when payments are received. We believe that the funds available through existing financing
	arrangements and forecasted cash flows will be sufficient to provide the necessary capital resources for our anticipated working capital needs, capital expenditures, investments, debt repayments,
	quarterly cash dividend payments, and common stock repurchases for at least the next twelve months. As of October&nbsp;31, 2016, cash and short-term investments held by our foreign subsidiaries that
	are not available to fund domestic operations unless repatriated were $105.5&nbsp;million. We currently do not intend to repatriate this cash held by our foreign subsidiaries; however, if
	circumstances changed and these funds were needed for our U.S. operations, we would be required to accrue and pay U.S. taxes to repatriate these funds. Determination of the unrecognized deferred tax
	liability related to these earnings is not practicable because of the complexities with its hypothetical calculation.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Seasonal
	cash requirements are financed from operations, cash on hand, and with short-term financing arrangements, including our $150.0&nbsp;million unsecured senior five-year revolving credit
	facility that expires in October 2019. Included in our $150.0&nbsp;million revolving credit facility is a $20.0&nbsp;million sublimit for standby letters of credit and a $20.0&nbsp;million
	sublimit for swingline loans. At our election, and with the approval of the named borrowers on the revolving credit facility and the election of the lenders to fund such increase, the aggregate
	maximum principal amount available under the facility may be increased by an amount up to $100.0&nbsp;million in aggregate. Funds are available under the revolving credit facility for working
	capital, capital expenditures, and other lawful purposes, including, but not limited to, acquisitions and stock repurchases. Interest expense on this credit line is determined based on a LIBOR rate
	(or other rates quoted by the Administrative Agent, Bank of America, N.A.) plus a basis point spread defined in the credit agreement. In addition, our non-U.S. operations maintain unsecured short-term
	lines of credit in the aggregate amount of $9.1&nbsp;million. These facilities bear interest at various rates depending on the rates in their respective countries of operation. As of
	October&nbsp;31, 2016 and October&nbsp;31, 2015 we had no outstanding short-term debt under these lines of credit. As of October&nbsp;31, 2016, we had $9.0&nbsp;million of outstanding letters
	of credit and $150.8&nbsp;million of unutilized availability under our credit agreements.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Additionally,
	as of October&nbsp;31, 2016, we had $353.9&nbsp;million outstanding in long-term debt that includes $100.0&nbsp;million of 7.8% debentures due June&nbsp;15, 2027,
	$123.7&nbsp;million of 6.625% senior notes due May&nbsp;1, 2037, $19.7&nbsp;million due to the former owners of the BOSS business, and $110.5&nbsp;million in an outstanding term loan. The term
	loan bears interest based on a LIBOR rate (or other rates quoted by the Administrative Agent, Bank of America, N.A.) plus a basis point spread defined in the credit agreement. The term loan can be
	repaid in part or in full at any time without penalty, but in any event must be paid in full by October 2019.
</FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	34
</FONT>
</P>
<HR NOSHADE>
<P STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;PAGE-BREAK-BEFORE:ALWAYS'>

<!-- ZEQ.=4,SEQ=34,EFW="2230524",CP="TORO COMPANY",DN="1",CHK=658210,FOLIO='34',FILE='DISK126:[16ZCF1.16ZCF41701]DO41701A.;37',USER='VRIVERA',CD='22-DEC-2016;05:11' -->
<A NAME="A2230524Z10-K_HTM_PAGE_DO41701_1_35">
</A>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<A HREF="#A2230524Z10-K_HTM_BG41701A_MAIN_TOC">
	Table of Contents
</A>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Our
	revolving and term loan credit facility contains standard covenants, including, without limitation, financial covenants, such as the maintenance of minimum interest coverage and maximum debt to
	earnings before interest, tax, depreciation, and amortization ("EBITDA") ratios; and negative covenants, which among other things, limit loans and investments, disposition of assets, consolidations
	and mergers, transactions with affiliates, restricted payments, contingent obligations, liens, and other matters customarily restricted in such agreements. Most of these restrictions are subject to
	certain minimum thresholds and exceptions. Under the revolving credit facility, we are not limited in the amount for payments of cash dividends and common stock repurchases as long as our debt to
	EBITDA ratio from the previous quarter compliance certificate is less than or equal to 3.25, provided that immediately after giving effect of any such proposed action, no default or event of default
	would exist. As of October&nbsp;31, 2016, we were not limited in the amount for payments of cash dividends and stock repurchases. We were in compliance with all covenants related to our credit
	agreement for our revolving credit facility as of October&nbsp;31, 2016, and we expect to be in compliance with all covenants during fiscal 2017. If we were out of compliance with any covenant
	required by this credit agreement following the applicable cure period, the banks could terminate their commitments unless we could negotiate a covenant waiver from the banks. In addition, our
	long-term senior notes, debentures, term loan, and any amounts outstanding under the revolving credit facility could become due and payable if we were unable to obtain a covenant waiver or refinance
	our short-term debt under our credit agreement. If our credit rating falls below and our debt to EBITDA ratio rises above 1.50, the basis point spread over LIBOR (or other rates quoted by the
	Administrative Agent, Bank of America, N.A.) we currently pay on outstanding debt under the credit agreement would increase. However, the credit commitment could not be cancelled by the banks based
	solely on a ratings downgrade. Our debt rating for long-term unsecured senior, non-credit enhanced debt was unchanged during fiscal 2016 by Standard and Poor's Ratings Group at BBB and by Moody's
	Investors Service at Baa3.
</FONT>
</P>

<!-- END OF USER-SPECIFIED TAGGED TABLE -->
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Our
	debt-to-capitalization ratio decreased in fiscal 2016 compared to fiscal 2015 primarily due to an increase in stockholders' equity from higher net earnings and repayments of our long-term debt,
	partially offset by an increase in dividends paid and repurchases of our common stock in fiscal 2016 as compared to fiscal 2015.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-LEFT:10.5PT;TEXT-INDENT:-10.5PT;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<A NAME="A2230524Z10-K_HTM_DO41701_CASH_DIVIDENDS">
</A>
<A NAME="A2230524Z10-K_HTM_TOC_DO41701_9">
</A>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:10.5PT;TEXT-INDENT:-10.5PT;" -->
	Cash Dividends
<BR>
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Each quarter in fiscal 2016, our Board of Directors declared a cash dividend of $0.15 per share, which was a 20&nbsp;percent
	increase over our cash dividend of $0.125 per share paid each quarter in fiscal 2015. As announced on December&nbsp;8, 2016, our Board of Directors increased our fiscal 2017 first quarter cash
	dividend by 16.7&nbsp;percent to $0.175 per share from the quarterly cash dividend paid in the first quarter of fiscal 2016.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-LEFT:10.5PT;TEXT-INDENT:-10.5PT;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<A NAME="A2230524Z10-K_HTM_DO41701_STOCK_SPLIT">
</A>
<A NAME="A2230524Z10-K_HTM_TOC_DO41701_10">
</A>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:10.5PT;TEXT-INDENT:-10.5PT;" -->
	Stock Split
<BR>
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	On August&nbsp;18, 2016, we announced that our Board of Directors declared a two-for-one stock split of our common stock, effected
	in the form of a 100&nbsp;percent stock dividend. The stock split dividend was distributed or paid on September&nbsp;16, 2016, to stockholders of record as of September&nbsp;1, 2016. As a result
	of this action, 54.5&nbsp;million shares were issued to stockholders of record as of September&nbsp;1, 2016. The par value of the common stock remains at $1.00 per share and, accordingly,
	approximately $54.5&nbsp;million was transferred from retained earnings to common stock. Earnings and dividends declared per share and weighted average shares outstanding are presented in this
	report after the effect of the 100&nbsp;percent stock dividend. The two-for-one stock split is reflected in the share amounts in all periods presented in this report.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-LEFT:10.5PT;TEXT-INDENT:-10.5PT;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<A NAME="A2230524Z10-K_HTM_DO41701_SHARE_REPURCHASE_PLAN">
</A>
<A NAME="A2230524Z10-K_HTM_TOC_DO41701_11">
</A>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:10.5PT;TEXT-INDENT:-10.5PT;" -->
	Share Repurchase Plan
<BR>
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	During fiscal 2016, we continued repurchasing shares of our common stock in the open market, thereby reducing our shares outstanding.
	In addition, our repurchase program provided shares for use in connection with our equity compensation plans. As of October&nbsp;31, 2016, 7,692,715 shares remained available for repurchase under
	our Board authorization. We expect to continue repurchasing shares of our common stock in fiscal 2017, depending upon market conditions.
</FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	35
</FONT>
</P>

<DL COMPACT>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-9PT;'>
<FONT SIZE=1>
<SUP>
	1
</SUP>
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=1>
	Share and per share data have been adjusted for all periods presented to reflect the impact of our two-for-one stock split effective
	September&nbsp;16, 2016.
<BR>
<BR>
</FONT>
</DD>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-9PT;'>
<FONT SIZE=1>
<SUP>
	2
</SUP>
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=1>
	Does
	not include shares of our common stock surrendered by employees to satisfy minimum tax withholding obligations upon vesting of restricted stock granted under our
	stock-based compensation plans.
</FONT>
</DD>
</DL>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=1>
<A NAME="A2230524Z10-K_HTM_DQ41701_CUSTOMER_FINANCING_ARRANGEMENTS">
</A>
<A NAME="A2230524Z10-K_HTM_TOC_DQ41701_1">
</A>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:10.5PT;TEXT-INDENT:-10.5PT;" -->
	Customer Financing Arrangements
<BR>
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<I>
	Wholesale Financing.
</I>
</B>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	We are party to a joint venture with TCFIF, established as Red
	Iron, the primary purpose of which is to provide inventory financing to certain distributors and dealers of our products in the U.S. that enables them to carry representative inventories of our
	products. Under a separate arrangement, TCFCFC provides inventory financing to dealers of our products in Canada. Under these financing arrangements, down payments are not required and, depending on
	the finance program for each product line, finance charges are incurred by us, shared between us and the distributor and/or the dealer, or paid by the distributor or dealer. Red Iron retains a
	security interest in the distributors' and dealers' financed inventories, and those inventories are monitored regularly. Financing terms to the distributors and dealers require payment as the
	equipment, which secures the indebtedness, is sold to customers or when payment terms become due, whichever occurs first. Rates are generally indexed to LIBOR plus a fixed percentage that differs
	based on whether the financing is for a distributor or dealer. Rates may also vary based on the product that is financed. Red Iron financed $1,713.6&nbsp;million of new receivables for dealers and
	distributors during fiscal 2016, of which $371.1&nbsp;million was outstanding as of October&nbsp;31, 2016.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Some
	independent international dealers continue to finance their products with a third-party financing company. This third-party financing company purchased $28.9&nbsp;million of receivables from us
	during fiscal 2016, of which $12.3&nbsp;million was outstanding as of October&nbsp;31, 2016.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	We
	enter into limited inventory repurchase agreements with third party financing companies and Red Iron for receivables financed by them. As of October&nbsp;31, 2016, we were contingently liable to
	repurchase up to a maximum amount of $10.4&nbsp;million of inventory related to receivables under these financing arrangements. We have repurchased immaterial amounts of inventory from third party
	financing companies and Red Iron over the past three fiscal years. However, a decline in retail sales or financial difficulties of our distributors or dealers could cause this situation to change and
	thereby require us to repurchase financed product up to but not exceeding our limited obligation, which could have an adverse effect on our operating results.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	We
	continue to provide financing in the form of open account terms to home centers and mass retailers; general line irrigation dealers; international distributors and dealers other than the Canadian
	distributors and dealers to whom Red Iron provides financing arrangements; micro-irrigation dealers and distributors; government customers; and rental companies.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<I>
	End-User Financing.
</I>
</B>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	We have agreements with third party financing companies to provide lease-financing options to golf course and sports fields and
	grounds equipment customers in the U.S. and select countries in Europe. The purpose of these agreements is to increase sales by giving buyers of our products alternative financing options when
	purchasing our products. We have no contingent liabilities for residual value or credit collection risk under these agreements with third party financing companies.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	From
	time to time, we enter into agreements where we provide recourse to third-party finance companies in the event of default by the customer for lease payments to the third-party finance company.
	Our maximum exposure for credit collection under those arrangements as of October&nbsp;31, 2016 was $4.9&nbsp;million.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Termination
	or any material change to the terms of our end-user financing arrangements, availability of credit for our customers, including any delay in securing replacement credit sources, or
	significant financed product repurchase requirements could have a material adverse impact on our future operating results.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<I>
	Distributor Financing.
</I>
</B>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	From time to time, we enter into long-term loan agreements with some distributors. These transactions are used for expansion of the
	distributors' businesses, acquisitions, refinancing working capital agreements, or facilitation of ownership changes. As of October&nbsp;31, 2016, we had an outstanding note receivable in the amount
	of $0.9&nbsp;million, which is included in other current and long-term assets on our consolidated balance sheet.
</FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	36
</FONT>
</P>

<EFX_BALANCE_SHEET>
<A NAME="FIS_BALANCE_SHEET"></A>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-0PT;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<A NAME="A2230524Z10-K_HTM_DQ41701_OFF-BALANCE_SHEET_ARRA__DQ402310">
</A>
<A NAME="A2230524Z10-K_HTM_TOC_DQ41701_2">
</A>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-0PT;" -->
	Off-Balance Sheet Arrangements and Contractual
<BR>
	Obligations
<BR>
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
